## Limitations

This report is limited by the availability of empirical data specifically from countries that have implemented a voting age of 16. While there is substantial advocacy and theoretical support for lowering the voting age, real-world data is primarily drawn from a few countries, such as Austria. Additionally, the report relies on sources that may have inherent biases, either in favor of or against lowering the voting age. Further research and longitudinal studies would be beneficial to fully understand the long-term impacts of such a policy change.